{
  "stem": "26111.6",
  "chunk_idx": 1,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 7.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And my parents shortly after that-- all this I found out much later-- made-- took steps to-- took the first steps in making the arrangements to go-- to try and go over the border illegally, leave Germany illegally.",
      "word_count": 38
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Because the legal ways had been exhausted, and there was just no way out for them.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And they knew that they would be deported sooner or later-- rather sooner than later.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So the-- they were taken up with other tasks [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] and concerns.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And I couldn't say now whether the last message-- clearly, it did not get, get to me.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Any letter wasn't written any later than the time that they left, sometime in '43-- that they left the house and went into hiding, which they did for a time before trying to-- trying the border crossing.",
      "word_count": 37
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Did you then eventually learn what happened to your parents?",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "After my sister had been deported, they, they figured that, that there was no longer any reason for them to, to stay around.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "There wasn't my sister to protect.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "There wasn't-- the only thing that they could do is to try and get out at all costs, including illegally.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And it was a big risk.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "But they had to take it, they felt.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So they left their house and moved into the apartment of a close family friend-- non-Jewish.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "She already had been a friend ever since we moved to Berlin, and-- or even before.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And this was a lady who was the wife of the architect Mies van der Rohe-- the one that was rather famous and built the buildings in Chicago.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "What was her name?",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Ada, A-D-A.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And the surname was a-- sounds more like a Dutch name.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But they were German.",
      "word_count": 4
    }
  ],
